<!--
VOICING PLAN (4105 — Christ Jesus Lay In Death's Strong Bands):
- Key: C (no sig) but D-Aeolian/Dorian modal tonal center.
- Bars 1-8: lighter 2-note RH / 3-note LH texture. Open fifths and thirds.
  - Beat-by-beat chord changes follow the melody's chromatic passing chords.
  - "E" chord (non-diatonic) treated as Em substitute (G-B in RH, E-B-E in LH).
  - "D major" chord treated as Dm (F# omitted for lever harp).
  - "Bb" chord spelled out with accid="f" on B notes (non-diatonic but present in the ABC).
  - "G" (non-diatonic major) treated as Gm or G-D-B open voicing.
- Bars 6-8: 7th chords added (Em7, Am7, Dm7) for richness on the repeat.
- Bars 9-16: fuller texture — 3-4 notes RH, 3-4 notes LH, wider range.
  - Bar 9: ascending RH arpeggio (D-F-A-C) against sustained LH.
  - Bar 10: full 4-note LH voicings.
  - Bar 12: high RH reaching up to G5 at the climax (e5 in melody).
  - Bar 15: Bb and Gm chords bring the accidentals into full voicing.
- Final bar 16: unison root-position Dm from bottom (D2) to top (A4).

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 2→3: RH G4-B4 → A4-C5 → G4-B4 oscillation mirrors melody's G-A-c motion.
- Bar 7: RH descends C5-E5 → B4-D5 → A4-C5 → F4-A4 while LH ascends (contrary motion).
- Bar 12: Peak — RH reaches E5-G5 when melody is at e5. LH stays low (G2-D3).
- Bar 14: LH inner voice E→G→A→E forms a smooth inner line.
- Bar 15: Bb-F-Gm-Dm provides a satisfying modal cadential approach.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-5: Light — 2-note RH, 2-3 note LH. Modal opening establishes Dm character.
- Bars 6-8: Medium — 7th chord enrichment on the repeat.
- Bars 9-12: Full — climbing to high D/E in melody, wide range in both hands.
- Bars 13-16: Convergence — stepwise descent to low Dm final chord. Pedal D2 resonates.
-->
